2.	What is the difference between value type and reference type variables? What is 
boxing and unboxing?
  A variable of a value type contains an instance of the variable. A reference type contains a reference address to an instance of that type. Values are stored in the stack while references are stored in the heap.
Boxing is the process of converting a value to an object or interface type. The value is wrapped inside a System.Object instance and stores it in the heap. Unboxing extracts the value from the object. 

3.	What is meant by the terms managed resource and unmanaged resource in .NET
Managed resources are resources that can be freed up by the garbage collector. Unmanage resources describes values that are not under the control of the garbage collector.

